text:
This is a bit random, but i think I’ve finally gotten to a point I don’t know what “staples” I’m missing... it’s a bit weird since I’ve been slowly picking them up (lands, removal, etc etc) thanks to EDHREC.

So... What are less common staples that you always tend to have copies of? Things that aren’t as obvious as say, fetches?
Before I started buying/selling collections, sol ring
Or ponder for my blue decks

Things you may not want in every deck but you'll want at some point and probably don't have just lying around: Berserk, Hatred, Sylvan Library, Land Tax, Necropotence, Path to Exile, Beast Within, Chaos Warp, Blapshemous Act, Austere Command, Toxic Deluge, Supreme Verict, Harmonize,
[[$toxic deluge]]
Ex Map and Wayfarer's Bauble, Kindred Discovery
(sigh)…
Cyclonic rift if you run blue of any kind
Deluge will hit 25 again before it hits 10
Sad but true
Who knows…that could be in the next masters set
I mean…if they can plan it before it hits $25 they’re more likely to do it..
Sudden Spoiling, Heroic Intervention, Scavenger Grounds, Mystic Remora, Blind Obedience. I like to have 1-2 copies of every Signet and Talisman lying around too

Thanks, team. That’s exactly what I was asking for.

Sylvan and Land Tax always weird to me. Like do I NEED them or not... but that also comes from never playing them before.
I probably should pick up Sylvan.
You need them
I love me some land tax. I didn't buy any when battlebond came out because I'm a dumber
Land Tax for me is a white/boros thing, where not only do you not have ramp, but it turns into a great draw engine w Scroll Rack

text: Stole your question Mason
Cool with me! The more input the better.
<@U33EGB4TX> they’re still around the same price. Battlebond has mostly stabilized. Plus I saw a rumor floating around another wave was being put into the wild.
Think the issue with common staples and things like land tax is the price of them dont warrant the staple itself
Yea, I heard/saw that too
Everyone can use a rhystic study wt 5 dollars, a land tax though? Ehhh
A staple is an auto include, those are luxuries
Like best example is mana crypt
That would be an auto include
land tax isn’t really a luxury in many white decks
But... gl affording that
Did the price go down significantly? I remember before that was expensive
[[$land tax]]
Ah that's better. Still too much for me as a staple but..  I remember it was like 30

That’s always a concern for me. I only have 1-ofs of a lot of things (especially fetches) because of price.
It wasn’t an issue before I started addin more decks, so now I’m needing to worry about my mana bases more
Yeah I also hit a point where I have sp many decks but then I had to split resources... which is never fun
This is a big deal for me because I tend to stick to the same colors
I only own one Vampiric Tutor
But I own 4 decks that currently run Black. And I have 4 more Commanders with Black set off to the side.
Nope, five. I have FIVE Bxx Commanders off to the side.
Sounds like you all have some Sophie's Choice type decisions to make
Something my play group does to combat this is we allow proxies of certain cards, as long as you own it or other special circumstance like cradle being an insane price
What, you haven't sold off a kidney to pay for a Cradle yet?
I sired a baseball team at the local...bank to pay for my duals
I really enjoy playing with the budget Cradle replacements like Growing Rites. Good card.
That team isn't very good at baseball though
Growing rites is so good
Crytolith Rite is also good if slow.
Baseball teams eh... I used to "invest" in cockfighting.
You could say I was doing the same thing at the bank
Zing

I run both Rite and Itlimoc in my Emmara. Both are houses.
Rite is one of those cards I feel like could go anywhere but I have trouble making room for it.
The ponder effect is so good
I have Cryp Rite in Najeela.
It's nuts
Sometimes
I’m surprised we’re letting <@U33EGB4TX> get away with a Sophie’s Choice reference that only <@U4V5EHQ2G>, <@U286Q175Y> and me gets…
because…old(er in some cases)
I get it obviously
that remains to be seen
<@U32LRG9NU> gets it
I got it too :joy:
That movie is older than 75% of the staff
You do know it was a book first, right?
Which means it's older than all of us
Nope
Was the book better?
Not me
Did the book have Meryl Streep? No? Question asked and answered…
Solid point
<@U4V5EHQ2G> there are so many responses to our tweet saying Reliquary tower and a couple Vedlaken Orrery....
Trolls
You forgot the #
Darksteel plate is nearing a staple for me, especially since the reprint. Though I do only have 2
Link?
To?
Also Henry, I laughed when I saw your tweet at DJ about Brawlington
I do my part.
Earlier you mentioned responses to your reliquary tower tweet, etc.
Oh
I posted the tweet up above but for the sake of Henry and technology...

text: Voltron i guess. Seems ok since it can be unblockable i guess
Nothing like holding a bunch of auras until turn 8
Feels more like a control deck to me.
At least that's how it wrecks me on Arena :disappointed:
Haven't seen any Chromium decks at my EDH night, so can't say how it works out as a commander.
But ya, having a basically invincible three-turn evasive clock seems good as a control finisher.
Having Flash really helps. Counter anything that might stop Chrome from hitting the dome.
Something I chuckled at is how they shoehorned Chromium's ability into the MTG Story columns over the summer.
<@U33EGB4TX> Jumbo Commander replied on the Twitters by saying Singleton has convinced him that he wishes he had more opportunity to play Brawl.
